cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.SE 

This paper discusses practical attacks on DNS resolvers, which fall under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attacks involve exploiting IP fragmentation, which is a networking concept (cs.NI). The paper also discusses traffic analysis and covert channels, which are topics in information theory and security (cs.SI). The attacks are related to the functioning of DNS, which is a distributed system (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of standard resolver software and DNS name servers, which are topics in software engineering (cs.SE).
